processes.name: pemPath
processes.description: Select where to create the key folder

processes.name: CopyOldLogsToS3Bucket
processes.description: Script to move old logs to s3. If you have more than 7 logs saved, it will start moving them to s3 from oldest to newest leaving only 7 in the instance

params.value:
#!/bin/bash
  
n=$(ls $path | wc -l)
if [ $n -gt 7 ];
then
        j=$(($n - 7))
        for ((i=1; i<=$j; i++))
        do
                old=$(ls -lt $path | tail -1 | awk '{ print $9 }')
                aws s3 mv $path/$old s3://$bucket/
        done
fi
params.name: CONTENT

processes.name: Execution
processes.preRun:
var resultPath= "export path='" + kaholo.execution.configuration.pathLog + "'"
var resultBucket= "export bucket='" + kaholo.execution.configuration.bucket + "'"
var result = resultPath + "; " + resultBucket + ";  bash CopyOldLogsToS3Bucket"

processes.name: Setup Script
processes.description: The script is saved in a directory on the server
processes.preRun: var command = "scp -i " + pathFile + " " + pathScript + " " + kaholo.execution.configuration.user + "@" + kaholo.execution.configuration.host + ":/home/" + kaholo.execution.configuration.user
